 "Cells" -> {<|"Data" -> ".md\n<Callout type=\"tip\">\nPack vertices and \
colors into a single symbol (like `complex2D` above). `\"VertexFence\"` \
prevents races between the index and vertex buffers, but it can't protect \
against partial updates to separate attributes.\n</Callout>\n\n## Going \
3D\n\nThe 3D story is the same \[LongDash] `GraphicsComplex` maps directly to \
THREE.js `BufferAttribute` objects written into GPU memory. The only \
difference is you now also have `VertexNormals` for lighting.\n\nLet's start \
with a dodecahedron:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "2ca4f094-608d-4a8a-ac8f-f3aec985fd14", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "<Callout type=\"tip\">\nPack vertices and colors into a \
single symbol (like `complex2D` above). `\"VertexFence\"` prevents races \
between the index and vertex buffers, but it can't protect against partial \
updates to separate attributes.\n</Callout>\n\n## Going 3D\n\nThe 3D story is \
the same \[LongDash] `GraphicsComplex` maps directly to THREE.js \
`BufferAttribute` objects written into GPU memory. The only difference is you \
now also have `VertexNormals` for lighting.\n\nLet's start with a \
dodecahedron:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
