   <|"Data" -> "### Texture mapping in 3D\n\nUV coordinates work identically \
to the 2D case:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "274170c0-a445-4824-b18e-6d5270855f7a", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "img = ExampleData[{\"TestImage\", \"Lena\"}];\nGraphics3D[{\n \
 Texture[img],\n  GraphicsComplex[\n    {{-1, -1, 0}, {1, -1, 0}, {1, 1, 0}, \
{-1, 1, 0}},\n    Polygon[{1, 2, 3, 4}],\n    VertexTextureCoordinates -> \
{{0, 1}, {0, 0}, {1, 0}, {1, 1}}\n  ]\n}]", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "7cfbabc5-61fe-4653-b4ac-39913c4fc7ca", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n## Animating 3D meshes\n\n### 10,000 vertices at 30 \
fps\n\nHere's a 100\[Times]100 grid \[LongDash] that's 10,000 vertices and \
~20,000 triangles \[LongDash] animated in real time:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "8f33e650-58c4-4526-9a3d-12fcc1a3a6eb", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "## Animating 3D meshes\n\n### 10,000 vertices at 30 \
fps\n\nHere's a 100\[Times]100 grid \[LongDash] that's 10,000 vertices and \
~20,000 triangles \[LongDash] animated in real time:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "5f0c5707-fa8d-4312-99c7-7bc903f50401", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "vertices = Flatten[Table[{i,j, 0}, {i,1.0,100.0,1.0}, {j, \
1.0,100.0,1.0}],1];\nidx[i_, j_] := (i - 1) 100 + j;\ntris = Flatten[\n  \
Table[\n    {\n      {idx[i, j],     idx[i + 1, j], idx[i, j + 1]},\n      \
{idx[i + 1, j], idx[i + 1, j + 1], idx[i, j + 1]}\n    },\n    {i, 1, 100 - \
1},\n    {j, 1, 100 - 1}\n  ],\n  2\n];\n\nGraphicsComplex[vertices//Offload, \
Polygon[tris]]//Graphics3D", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "44acd233-ed7b-4d85-be7a-a4a2c1a422fd", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nThe triangle indices are computed once and stay fixed. \
Only the vertex positions change each frame \[LongDash] which means only the \
position buffer gets updated on the GPU:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "9c9558c8-8e9e-4d22-98d6-077b3d636666", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "The triangle indices are computed once and stay fixed. Only \
the vertex positions change each frame \[LongDash] which means only the \
position buffer gets updated on the GPU:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "a237669f-2d8e-4116-9e3c-2a2e04946592", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "gen := Module[\n  {t = AbsoluteTime[], s = 0.13, cx, cy},\n  \
cx = 50 + 20 Cos[0.5 t];\n  cy = 50 + 20 Sin[0.7 t];\n  vertices = Flatten[\n \
   Table[\n      {\n        i, j,\n         5 Sin[s i + t] +\n         5 \
Sin[s j - 1.3 t] +\n        3 12 Exp[-((i - cx)^2 + (j - cy)^2)/120.]\n      \
},\n      {i, 1., 100.}, {j, 1., 100.}\n    ],\n    1\n  ]\n];\n\nDo[gen; \
Pause[1/30.0], {500}];", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "50af590d-3147-4e9c-ae2d-d8db50709ce2", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n### Adding dynamic color\n\nSame grid, but now we also \
update a color buffer each frame. Two GPU buffers updated per frame \
\[LongDash] positions and colors \[LongDash] still smooth:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "bd72f83e-41e2-489d-aa0e-55c751dfda8e", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "### Adding dynamic color\n\nSame grid, but now we also update \
a color buffer each frame. Two GPU buffers updated per frame \[LongDash] \
positions and colors \[LongDash] still smooth:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "92724129-1671-4907-a259-78c02ddaa45d", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "idx[i_, j_] := (i - 1) 100 + j;\ntris = Flatten[\n  Table[\n  \
  {\n      {idx[i, j],     idx[i + 1, j], idx[i, j + 1]},\n      {idx[i + 1, \
j], idx[i + 1, j + 1], idx[i, j + 1]}\n    },\n    {i, 1, 100 - 1},\n    {j, \
1, 100 - 1}\n  ],\n  2\n];\n\ncf = ColorData[\"DarkRainbow\"];\n\ngenData := \
Module[\n  {t = AbsoluteTime[], s = 0.12, verts, z, cols},\n\n  verts = \
Flatten[\n    Table[\n      {\n        i, j,\n        6 Sin[s i + 1.4 t] +\n  \
      5 Sin[s j - 1.1 t] +\n        3 Sin[s (i + j) + 0.6 t] +\n        8 \
Cos[0.5 s Sqrt[(i - 50.)^2 + (j - 50.)^2] - 1.8 t]\n      },\n      {i, 1., \
100.}, {j, 1., 100.}\n    ],\n    1\n  ];\n\n  z = verts[[All, 3]];\n\n  (* \
fixed range avoids color flicker *)\n  cols = (List@@cf[#]) &/@ Rescale[z, \
{-18, 18}];\n\n  data = {verts, \
cols};\n];\n\ngenData;\n\nGraphicsComplex[data[[1]]//Offload, Polygon[tris], \
VertexColors->Offload[data[[2]]]]//Graphics3D \n\nDo[genData; Pause[1/30.0];, \
{500}];", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "3b3f99b7-e1b2-4593-9f12-820cedeca811", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n### Animated surface with \
`AnimationFrameListener`\n\nFor a cleaner animation loop, use \
`AnimationFrameListener` instead of `Do` + `Pause`. This ties the computation \
to the browser's refresh cycle:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "605cb3f9-b548-4b37-bf6e-ab30a31e5397", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "### Animated surface with `AnimationFrameListener`\n\nFor a \
cleaner animation loop, use `AnimationFrameListener` instead of `Do` + \
`Pause`. This ties the computation to the browser's refresh cycle:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "9565bce0-904a-4302-85d0-e0fe98e9fcfe", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "(* Grid dimensions *)\nnx = 50; ny = 50;\n\n(* Triangle \
indices \[LongDash] generated once *)\nindices = Flatten[Table[\n  With[{v = \
(i - 1) ny + j},\n    {{v, v + 1, v + ny + 1}, {v, v + ny + 1, v + ny}}\n  \
],\n  {i, nx - 1}, {j, ny - 1}\n], 2];\n\n(* Generates {vertices, \
vertexColors} at time t *)\ngenerateFrame[t_] := Module[{verts, zVals, mn, \
mx},\n  verts = Flatten[Table[\n    With[{r = Sqrt[x^2 + y^2]},\n      {x, \
y,\n        Sin[4 r - 2 t] Exp[-0.3 r] +\n        0.3 Sin[2 x - t] Cos[2 y + \
0.5 t]}\n    ],\n    {x, Subdivide[-2., 2., nx - 1]},\n    {y, Subdivide[-2., \
2., ny - 1]}\n  ], 1];\n\n  zVals = verts[[All, 3]];\n  {mn, mx} = \
MinMax[zVals];\n\n  {verts, Map[\n    With[{s = Rescale[#[[3]], {mn, mx}]},\n \
     List@@RGBColor[s, 0.15 + 0.35 s, 1. - 0.8 s]\n    ]&, verts\n  \
]}\n];\n\n(* Initialize *)\ncomplex = generateFrame[0.];\n\n(* Display \
*)\nGraphics3D[{GraphicsComplex[\n  Offload[complex[[1]]],\n  \
{Polygon[indices]},\n  VertexColors -> Offload[complex[[2]]]\n], \
EventHandler[AnimationFrameListener[complex//Offload], Function[Null,\n  \
complex = generateFrame[AbsoluteTime[]];\n]]}]", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "846000ef-2aa2-48b8-86d1-e544207f2f40", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n### Dynamic topology in 3D\n\nThe most demanding case: \
vertices, colors, __and__ triangle indices all changing every frame. Two \
orbiting holes punch through the mesh in real time:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "195a6370-69d0-4262-b145-3d1a0705a39a", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "### Dynamic topology in 3D\n\nThe most demanding case: \
vertices, colors, __and__ triangle indices all changing every frame. Two \
orbiting holes punch through the mesh in real time:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "b7c20354-77ca-42a3-8b0d-513bc030289d", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "(* Grid dimensions *)\nnx = 50; ny = 50;\n\n(* All triangle \
indices *)\nallIndices = Flatten[Table[\n  With[{v = (i - 1) ny + j},\n    \
{{v, v + 1, v + ny + 1}, {v, v + ny + 1, v + ny}}\n  ],\n  {i, nx - 1}, {j, \
ny - 1}\n], 2];\n\nxs = Subdivide[-2., 2., nx - 1];\nys = Subdivide[-2., 2., \
ny - 1];\n\n(* Precompute centroid XY of each triangle for fast filtering \
*)\ngridXY = Flatten[Table[{x, y}, {x, xs}, {y, ys}], 1];\ntriCX = \
(gridXY[[#[[1]], 1]] + gridXY[[#[[2]], 1]] + gridXY[[#[[3]], 1]]) / 3. & /@ \
allIndices;\ntriCY = (gridXY[[#[[1]], 2]] + gridXY[[#[[2]], 2]] + \
gridXY[[#[[3]], 2]]) / 3. & /@ allIndices;\n\ngenerateFrame[t_] := \
Module[{verts, zVals, mn, mx, h1, h2, d1, d2, mask},\n  verts = \
Flatten[Table[\n    With[{r = Sqrt[x^2 + y^2]},\n      {x, y,\n        Sin[4 \
r - 2 t] Exp[-0.3 r] +\n        0.3 Sin[2 x - t] Cos[2 y + 0.5 t]}\n    ],\n  \
  {x, xs}, {y, ys}\n  ], 1];\n\n  zVals = verts[[All, 3]];\n  {mn, mx} = \
MinMax[zVals];\n\n  (* Two holes orbiting the center *)\n  h1 = {1.3 Cos[0.8 \
t], 1.3 Sin[0.8 t]};\n  h2 = {1.3 Cos[0.8 t + Pi], 1.3 Sin[0.8 t + Pi]};\n\n  \
(* Vectorized distance computation *)\n  d1 = Sqrt[(triCX - h1[[1]])^2 + \
(triCY - h1[[2]])^2];\n  d2 = Sqrt[(triCX - h2[[1]])^2 + (triCY - \
h2[[2]])^2];\n\n  (* Keep triangles outside both holes *)\n  mask = \
UnitStep[d1 - 0.55] UnitStep[d2 - 0.55];\n\n  {Pick[allIndices, mask, 1], \
{verts,\n   Map[With[{s = Rescale[#[[3]], {mn, mx}]},\n     List @@ \
RGBColor[s, 0.15 + 0.35 s, 1. - 0.8 s]] &, verts]}}\n];\n\n(* Initialize \
*)\n{indices, complex} = generateFrame[0.];\n\n(* Display \[LongDash] note \
Offload on indices for dynamic topology *)\nGraphics3D[{GraphicsComplex[\n  \
Offload[complex[[1]]],\n  {Polygon[Offload[indices]]},\n  VertexColors -> \
Offload[complex[[2]]],\n  \"VertexFence\" -> True\n], \
EventHandler[AnimationFrameListener[complex // Offload], Function[Null,\n  \
{indices, complex} = generateFrame[AbsoluteTime[]];\n]]}]", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "fd72ca52-0e38-4997-a7d2-e8807ca6a748", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n## Hijacking plot functions as geometry \
generators\n\nHere's a fun trick: you can use standard plotting functions \
like `ParametricPlot3D` as mesh generators, then feed their output into a \
`GraphicsComplex` that you control. This gives you the best of both worlds \
\[LongDash] automatic tessellation from the plotter, and full GPU-level \
control over the result.\n\nDefine a function that interpolates between a \
torus and a seashell:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "b00954bc-fd10-427c-af14-f97f1d6f4f95", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "## Hijacking plot functions as geometry generators\n\nHere's \
a fun trick: you can use standard plotting functions like `ParametricPlot3D` \
as mesh generators, then feed their output into a `GraphicsComplex` that you \
control. This gives you the best of both worlds \[LongDash] automatic \
tessellation from the plotter, and full GPU-level control over the \
result.\n\nDefine a function that interpolates between a torus and a \
seashell:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "9b145005-0a8e-4213-9265-793ac9e4a43d", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".\nwolfram title=\"cell 1\"\nsample[t_] := With[{\n   complex \
= ParametricPlot3D[\n     (1 - t) * {\n       (2 + Cos[v]) * Cos[u],\n       \
(2 + Cos[v]) * Sin[u],\n       Sin[v]\n     } + t * {\n       1.16^v * Cos[v] \
* (1 + Cos[u]),\n       -1.16^v * Sin[v] * (1 + Cos[u]),\n       -2 * 1.16^v \
* (1 + Sin[u]) + 1.0\n     },\n     {u, 0, 2\\[Pi]},\n     {v, -\\[Pi], \
\\[Pi]},\n     MaxRecursion -> 2,\n     Mesh -> None\n   ][[1, 1]]\n   },\n  \
{\n   complex[[1]],\n   Cases[complex[[2]], _Polygon, 6] // First // First,\n \
  complex[[3, 2]]\n  }\n]", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "a530056e-51ff-483a-98e6-c3e686a1f7bf", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nNow wire it up with a slider \[LongDash] the plotter \
generates new geometry, and `GraphicsComplex` pushes it to the GPU:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "b1fa924f-fc94-49a7-8f19-579627a0a236", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Now wire it up with a slider \[LongDash] the plotter \
generates new geometry, and `GraphicsComplex` pushes it to the GPU:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "068e1a08-f7f4-4285-ae14-174095deec37", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Module[{\n    VerticesAndNormals = {{}, {}}, indices = {}\n  \
},\n    {\n      EventHandler[InputRange[0,1,0.1,0], Function[value,\n        \
With[{res  = sample[value]},\n          indices = res[[2]];\n          \
VerticesAndNormals = {res[[1]], res[[3]]};\n        ];\n      ]],\n\n      \
With[{res  = sample[0.0]},\n          indices = res[[2]];\n          \
VerticesAndNormals = {res[[1]], res[[3]]};\n      ];\n      \n      \
Graphics3D[{\n        SpotLight[Red, 5 {1,1,1}], SpotLight[Blue, 5 \
{-1,-1,1}], \n        SpotLight[Green, 5 {1,-1,1}], \n        \
PointLight[Magenta, {10,10,10}],\n        \n        \
GraphicsComplex[Offload[VerticesAndNormals[[1]]], {\n          \
Polygon[Offload[indices]]\n        }, \
VertexNormals->Offload[VerticesAndNormals[[2]]], \"VertexFence\"->True]\n     \
   \n      }, Lighting->None]\n    } // Column // Panel \n]", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "5fe5998a-c2f3-4204-abcb-4cf24b883cc9", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n## Tips for smooth animations\n\nA few things to keep in \
mind when pushing `GraphicsComplex` to its limits:\n\n- __Use raw RGB lists__ \
for `VertexColors` \[LongDash] avoid symbolic colors like `Red` or `Hue[...]` \
in the hot path\n- __Pack related data__ into a single symbol (e.g. `data = \
{vertices, colors}`) to avoid partial-update races\n- __Enable \
`\"VertexFence\"`__ when updating both indices and vertex data \[LongDash] it \
ensures the GPU reads consistent state\n- __Prefer `AnimationFrameListener`__ \
over `Do[...; Pause[...]]` for browser-synced animation\n- __Triangles are \
fastest__ in 3D \[LongDash] quads and pentagons get tessellated \
anyway\n\n`GraphicsComplex` won't write your shaders for you, but it does \
give you a remarkably direct line from Wolfram Language arrays to GPU memory. \
For real-time visualization of simulations, generative art, or anything with \
thousands of moving parts \[LongDash] it's the right tool.", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "23ded51f-1ab3-41c6-a9e9-4c13ac7d94c5", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "## Tips for smooth animations\n\nA few things to keep in mind \
when pushing `GraphicsComplex` to its limits:\n\n- __Use raw RGB lists__ for \
`VertexColors` \[LongDash] avoid symbolic colors like `Red` or `Hue[...]` in \
the hot path\n- __Pack related data__ into a single symbol (e.g. `data = \
{vertices, colors}`) to avoid partial-update races\n- __Enable \
`\"VertexFence\"`__ when updating both indices and vertex data \[LongDash] it \
ensures the GPU reads consistent state\n- __Prefer `AnimationFrameListener`__ \
over `Do[...; Pause[...]]` for browser-synced animation\n- __Triangles are \
fastest__ in 3D \[LongDash] quads and pentagons get tessellated \
anyway\n\n`GraphicsComplex` won't write your shaders for you, but it does \
give you a remarkably direct line from Wolfram Language arrays to GPU memory. \
For real-time visualization of simulations, generative art, or anything with \
thousands of moving parts \[LongDash] it's the right tool.", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "24d3ee9c-9869-4463-9371-ba09fdd0e805", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "00e43f81-6b05-4ced-9e91-d681ba3cd82f"|>}, 
 "serializer" -> "jsfn4"|>
